prompt_templates.recommendation_explanation:
Project Profile:
{profile_json}

Scoring Engine Output:
{scored_tools_json}

For the top 3 tools in each category, write a structured explanation covering: (1) Why this tool fits this specific project, (2) Key integration considerations with their existing stack, (3) Risks and honest tradeoffs, (4) What maturity level is needed to operate it well. Be concise but specific. Format as JSON with tool_name, fit_summary, integration_notes, risks, maturity_required, confidence_level fields.

prompt_templates.comparison_mode:
Project Profile:
{profile_json}

Compare these tools side by side for this project:
{tool_list_json}

Return a JSON comparison matrix with criteria as rows and tools as columns. Criteria: setup_complexity, team_fit, cost_at_scale, community_support, cloud_integration, security_posture, learning_curve, vendor_risk. Score each 1-10 and add one sentence justification per cell.

prompt_templates.report_generation:
Project Profile:
{profile_json}

Full Recommendations:
{full_results_json}

Generate a complete professional Markdown report for this DevOps tool selection. Include: Executive Summary, Project Requirements Analysis, Recommended Toolchain (all categories), Tool-by-Tool Justifications, Risk Register, Implementation Roadmap (phased 0-30-60-90 days), Cost Estimate, Next Steps. Write for a technical audience. Use Markdown formatting with headers, tables, and bullet points.
